text: This obsoletes IRM 4.19.27, Campus Exam Return Selection and Workload Delivery Managements internal procedures.

This IRM is being made obsolete as of the date of this transmittal. This IRM was originally created response to a TIGTA audit requiring Examination Head Quarters to follow written procedures. No such IRM existed at the time of the issuance of the audit. This IRM was created as a stop-gap measure, so an IRM was put in place to comply with the new standards. In the meantime, a more complete and detailed IRM was being prepared that covered other areas of Examination Head Quarters. That IRM is now complete and can be found at IRM
, Campus Exam Return Selection, Delivery and Monitoring, which has now been published, and incorporates all the information that this IRM once contained. For all users, please refer to IRM
for further guidance, protocols ad procedural matters.
IRM 4.19.27, Campus Exam Return Selection and Workload Delivery Management, dated 3-19-2015 is obsolete as of the date of this transmittal.
